# PaceIQ Cursor Rules

## Kipcoachee AI
- The coach is always called Kipcoachee — never KipCoach, Kipcoach, or any other name
- Every conversational AI call MUST go through the coach-chat Edge Function which uses buildKipcoacheeSystemPrompt()
- System prompt lives in src/lib/kipcoachee/system-prompt.ts — never hardcode conversational prompts in components or other edge functions
- The edge function (supabase/functions/coach-chat/index.ts) has its own Deno-compatible copy of the prompt builder — keep both in sync
- Context is built by buildAthleteContext() in the edge function — never manually assemble context strings
- Temperature: 0.6 for chat, 0.4 for plan generation and structured JSON outputs
- Max tokens: 4096 for chat messages, 4000 for plan generation
- Groq model: llama-3.3-70b-versatile (primary), Gemini 2.0 Flash (fallback)
- Task-specific prompts (activity feedback, workout notes, philosophy) in other edge functions must still identify as "Kipcoachee — an elite AI running coach built into PaceIQ"

## Data
- Never show empty cards — always show meaningful empty states or suggest connecting data sources
- Never use created_at for activity dates — always use date or start_date_local
- Always filter activities by type = 'Run' unless explicitly showing all sports
- Use resolveCtlAtlTsb() helper for CTL/ATL/TSB — handles icu_ prefix fallbacks and TSB derivation

## Code Style
- No inline styles — always use Tailwind classes
- No any types in TypeScript
- Always handle loading and error states
- Never call Supabase directly from UI components — always use hooks (useActivities, useReadiness, etc.)
- Edge functions use Deno imports (https://deno.land/std, https://esm.sh/) — never npm imports
- Never use ## or ### markdown headers in coach responses — use **bold** for section titles

## Architecture
- src/lib/kipcoachee/ — canonical types and prompt (TypeScript, client-compatible)
- supabase/functions/coach-chat/ — main conversational AI endpoint
- supabase/functions/intervals-proxy/ — data sync + task-specific AI (activity notes, workout notes)
- supabase/functions/paceiq-generate-plan/ — structured plan generation
- supabase/functions/paceiq-philosophy/ — philosophy recommendation
- All AI calls go through Groq first, Gemini as fallback
